23/11/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica is making a landmark visit to Zagreb on Wednesday (23 November) -- the first by a Serbian prime minister in 15 years.
In an interview Tuesday with the Croatian news agency HINA, he noted the significant recent improvement in bilateral ties between the two former Yugoslav republics and said he believes that trend would continue, given the shared goal of EU integration.
At the same time, he noted that outstanding issues remain, such as refugee returns and clarifying the fate of missing persons.
In other news Tuesday, Croatia and Montenegro signed a bilateral agreement on increased police co-operation in fighting organised crime and illegal migration .It envisions better communication and the exchange of data and expertise.
(HRT, Novi list - 23/11/05;
HINA, Tanjug, Beta - 22/11/05)
